"""
inference.py
============
FastAPI real-time inference server for the hybrid fraud detection framework.

Paper
-----
"A Hybrid Deep Learning and Explainable AI Framework for Real-Time
Financial Fraud Detection in Dynamic Environments"

Deployment architecture (from paper Methodology section)
---------------------------------------------------------
"We package the inference pipeline including embedding extraction,
ensemble classification and SHAP explanation in Docker and make it
accessible through REST APIs generated using FastAPI.  Latency
monitoring is also involved so that predictions can satisfy
sub-millisecond limits."

"The classifier is strictly synchronous and explanations are
asynchronous on the serving path, so that p50 and p99 latency is
single-digit milliseconds and the SHAP artifact can reach analyst
consoles a few hundred milliseconds later without impacting the
customer experience."

"A lightweight governance layer stores the entire context of the
decision in terms of features, score, threshold, explanation, version
pins, and provenance of data."

Two-path serving design
-----------------------
  SYNCHRONOUS  (< 5 ms target):
    POST /predict
      raw features → preprocess → DNN encode → ensemble score
      → calibrate → threshold → fraud decision + reason codes

  ASYNCHRONOUS (< 500 ms, background task):
    The same request triggers a background task that runs TreeSHAP
    and appends the full attribution vector to an in-memory audit log
    accessible at GET /explain/{request_id}

Endpoints
---------
  POST /predict               — score a single transaction
  POST /predict/batch         — score a batch (up to 512 transactions)
  GET  /explain/{request_id}  — retrieve async SHAP explanation
  GET  /health                — liveness probe (used by Docker/K8s)
  GET  /metrics               — latency stats and throughput counters
  GET  /model/info            — model version, threshold, feature list

Usage
-----
  # Start server (development)
  uvicorn src.inference:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --workers 1

  # Score a transaction
  curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/predict \\
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \\
    -d '{"transaction_id": "TX_001", "V1": -1.36, "V2": -0.07,
         "Amount": 149.62, "log_amount": 5.01, "time_delta": 3.0,
         "amount_zscore_rolling": 0.4, "tx_velocity_100": 12,
         "tx_velocity_500": 48, "hour_of_day": 14, "is_night": 0,
         "amount_rolling_mean_100": 88.3, "amount_rolling_std_100": 44.1,
         "V3": 2.53, ...}'

  # Retrieve SHAP explanation (async, available within ~500 ms)
  curl http://localhost:8000/explain/TX_001
"""

